
Topics covered:
- K-Means clustering and hierarchical clustering with dendrograms
- Silhouette analysis for evaluating cluster quality

Resources:
- https://machinelearningmastery.com/the-beginners-guide-to-clustering-with-python/
- https://machinelearningmastery.com/k-means-cluster-evaluation-with-silhouette-analysis/

Hands-on:
- Implemented K-Means and Agglomerative Clustering on the Mall Customer
  Segmentation dataset
- Scaled Income and Spending Score features using StandardScaler since
  both methods are distance-based
- Ran the Elbow Method, tracking K-Means inertia across K=1 to 10
- Plotted a dendrogram using Ward linkage to inspect the merge structure
- Used Silhouette Score across K=2 to 10 to pick a concrete K rather than
  relying on the elbow plot alone
- Visualized clusters with 2D Plots
- Built a side-by-side comparison of K-Means vs hierarchical clustering
  on the same K

Result:
Clustering implemented end to end in a notebook - data load, scaling,
elbow, silhouette, final K-Means model, dendrogram, final hierarchical
model, comparison.
